1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,931
Then get the put service first attitude.

2
00:00:04,240 --> 00:00:10,610
It's perfectly natural, in fact it's highly desirable, to want to make money and accumulate wealth.

3
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:16,050
Money is power to give your family and yourself the standard of living they deserve.

4
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:18,931
Money is power to help the unfortunate.

5
00:00:19,201 --> 00:00:22,451
Money is one of the means to living life fully.

6
00:00:23,119 --> 00:00:29,250
Once criticized for urging people to make money, the great minister Russell H. Conwell,

7
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:35,730
author of Acres of Diamonds, said, Money printed your Bible, money builds your churches,

8
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:44,050
money sends your missionaries, and money pays your preachers, and you would not have many of them either if you did not pay them.

9
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:52,130
The person who says he wants to be poor usually suffers from a guilt complex or a feeling of inadequacy.

10
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:57,650
He's like the youngster who feels he can't make A's in school or make the football team,

11
00:00:57,760 --> 00:01:01,730
so he pretends he doesn't want to make A's or play football.

12
00:01:02,639 --> 00:01:05,569
Money, then, is a desirable objective.

13
00:01:05,679 --> 00:01:11,811
What's puzzling about money is the backward approach so many people use in trying to make it.

14
00:01:12,159 --> 00:01:15,891
Everywhere you see people with a money-first attitude.

15
00:01:16,079 --> 00:01:19,010
Yet these same people always have little money.

16
00:01:19,119 --> 00:01:19,650
Why?

17
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:20,931
Simply this.

18
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:31,569
People with a money-first attitude become so money-conscious that they forget money can't be harvested unless they plant the seeds that grow the money.

19
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:34,371
And the seed of money is service.

20
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:39,090
That's why put service first is an attitude that creates wealth.

21
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:43,090
Put service first and money takes care of itself.

22
00:01:43,679 --> 00:01:47,811
One summer evening, I was traveling by car through Cincinnati.

23
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,569
It was time for a gas up.

24
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:54,690
I stopped at an ordinary looking but surprisingly busy service station.

25
00:01:55,360 --> 00:02:00,610
Four minutes later, I knew why this particular service station was so popular.

26
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:07,170
After filling my car with gasoline, checking under the hood, and cleaning the outside of my windshield,

27
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:11,331
the attendant walked around to my side of the car and said, Pardon me,

28
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:13,250
sir, it's been a dusty day.

29
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:16,050
Let me clean the inside of your windshield.

30
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:22,050
Quickly and efficiently, he did a thorough job of cleaning the inside of my windshield,

31
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:26,770
something not one service station attendant in a hundred ever does.

32
00:02:27,679 --> 00:02:33,971
This little special service did more than improve my night visibility, and it improved a lot.

33
00:02:34,159 --> 00:02:36,371
It made me remember this station.

34
00:02:36,639 --> 00:02:41,650
It so happened that I made eight trips through Cincinnati during the next three months.

35
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:49,331
Each time, of course, I stopped at this station, and each time I got more service than I expected to get.

36
00:02:49,679 --> 00:02:54,931
Interesting, too, was the fact that each time I stopped, once it was 4 a.m.,

37
00:02:55,039 --> 00:02:57,650
there were other automobiles filling up also.

38
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:03,730
In all, I probably purchased about 100 gallons of gasoline from this station.

39
00:03:04,721 --> 00:03:10,290
The first time I stopped, the attendant could have thought to himself, this guy is from out of state.

40
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:13,170
Odds are 20 to 1 that he'll never be back.

41
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,971
Why do more than give him the routine treatment?

42
00:03:16,079 --> 00:03:18,130
He's only a one-time customer.

43
00:03:18,639 --> 00:03:21,971
But the attendants in that station didn't think that way.

44
00:03:22,159 --> 00:03:29,730
They put service first, and that's why they were busy pumping gasoline while other stations looked almost deserted.

45
00:03:30,319 --> 00:03:35,090
If the gasoline was any better than a dozen other brands, I didn't notice it,

46
00:03:35,119 --> 00:03:37,170
and the price was competitive.

47
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:43,490
The difference was service, and it was obvious that service was paying off in profits.

48
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:50,451
When the attendant on my first visit cleaned the inside of my windshield, he planted a money seed.

49
00:03:50,721 --> 00:03:55,490
Put service first, and money takes care of itself, always.

50
00:03:56,319 --> 00:04:00,451
The put service first attitude pays off in all situations.

